I think this might be the Louis Barth who was the subject of a New York Times article published on December 10, 1911:

<a href="http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9C07EEDD123AE633A25753C1A9649D946096D6CF">&quot;LONDON, Nov. 29. -- The most remarkable autograph album in existence is the property of Louis Barth of Arad, Hungary</a>. Herr Barth, who is a Government official, has made the completion of the album a lifework. He wants it to contain the signature of every celebrity of the world, and he has gone a long way toward accomplishing his object.&quot;

I'd surmise that the book he's holding in the photo is his autograph album. (PDF of the whole Times article is available at the link).
